Telson: Length of the lobe about twice the widest width; one to two long and robust spine(s) and some 1–6 long setae on the distal margin, length of which is 80–90 percent of the whole length of the telson; one to four groups of setae ( 1–2 each) on dorsal surface of the lobes, sometimes accompanied by another long spine (Fig.
